    <p><span itemprop="name">The following ITIL terms and acronyms (<i>information objects</i>) are used in the Application Management process to represent process outputs and inputs:</span> </p>
    <p>&#160;</p>
    <p><b><span id="Skills_Inventory" itemprop="itemListElement">Skills Inventory</span></b> </p>
    <ul>
      <li itemprop="description">The Skills Inventory identifies the skills required to deliver IT services (now and in future), as well as the individuals who possess those skills. The Skills Inventory is the basis for developing training plans for individual employees. </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <!-- end of schema.org/ItemList -->
  <p class="mw-empty-elt"> </p>
